GameClock

This package is used to build a clock for playing Chess or GO
using the mouse buttons of a laptop as clock buttons. Keyboard
is also separated into two sides, so keys could be used instead 
mouse.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install


Alternatively, to install with Module::Build, you can use the following commands:

    perl Build.PL
    ./Build
    ./Build test
    ./Build install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc GameClock

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/GameClock

    CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=GameClock

    AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/GameClock

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/GameClock

